169
00:09:47,416 --> 00:09:49,125
I don't get paid again
until next week!

170
00:09:49,208 --> 00:09:51,250
[RINDOU]
Rinka.

171
00:09:51,333 --> 00:09:53,500
This white-haired girl
everybody's up in arms about

172
00:09:53,583 --> 00:09:54,666
is you, isn't it?

173
00:09:54,750 --> 00:09:55,833
[RINKA]
Huh?

174
00:09:55,916 --> 00:09:57,291
I wasn't sure at first,
but it looked like

175
00:09:57,375 --> 00:09:58,541
she was saving
this little girl from

176
00:09:58,625 --> 00:10:00,041
some creepy dudes in a van.

177
00:10:00,125 --> 00:10:01,875
Well, and then the
guy in the weird mask

178
00:10:01,958 --> 00:10:04,375
saved those old ladies,
which was totally awesome!

179
00:10:04,458 --> 00:10:06,250
The long and short of it is,
whoever they are,

180
00:10:06,333 --> 00:10:07,541
I owe them my life.

181
00:10:07,625 --> 00:10:09,833
Okay, before you
start freaking out.

182
00:10:09,916 --> 00:10:13,208
We weren't doing anything bad,
just giving some folks a hand--

183
00:10:13,291 --> 00:10:15,416
[RINDOU]
Damn it, Rinka!

184
00:10:17,458 --> 00:10:19,375
[KYOTARO] Well, naturally
he's gonna worry.

185
00:10:19,458 --> 00:10:20,625
He's your dad.

186
00:10:20,708 --> 00:10:22,416
And you make no effort
to disguise yourself.

187
00:10:22,500 --> 00:10:23,666
Oh, whatever.

188
00:10:23,750 --> 00:10:25,958
My hair goes white,
what more do you want?

189
00:10:28,041 --> 00:10:29,791
[MURASAKI]
I think the publicity is great.

190
00:10:29,875 --> 00:10:32,833
People are crazy about you guys.

191
00:10:32,916 --> 00:10:33,958
[BOY 3A]
Oh crap, it's her!

192
00:10:34,041 --> 00:10:36,333
[BOY 3B]
Let's get out of here!

193
00:10:37,666 --> 00:10:38,916
[KYOTARO]
Friends of yours, I'm guessing?

194
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:41,500
[MURASAKI] Just some boys
from the neighborhood.

195
00:10:43,208 --> 00:10:44,625
[MURASAKI] My house is
just around the corner

196
00:10:44,708 --> 00:10:46,083
if you wanna head back.

197
00:10:46,166 --> 00:10:48,208
We're cool with walking you
the rest of the way home.

198
00:10:48,291 --> 00:10:49,875
It's probably better
we know where you live,

199
00:10:49,958 --> 00:10:51,583
just in case.

200
00:10:55,750 --> 00:10:57,041
[RINKA]
Whoa!

201
00:10:57,125 --> 00:10:59,791
Not to be rude, but is
your family, like, loaded?

202
00:10:59,875 --> 00:11:02,500
That's not exactly it, no.

203
00:11:02,583 --> 00:11:03,333
[MALE SUBORDINATES]
Welcome home,

204
00:11:03,416 --> 00:11:05,708
young mistress Murasaki.

205
00:11:05,791 --> 00:11:08,166
That wasn't quite the welcome
I was expecting to get.

206
00:11:08,250 --> 00:11:09,875
[EDOYAMA]
This is a rare pleasure.

207
00:11:09,958 --> 00:11:11,125
[KYOTARO, RINKA]
Uh--

208
00:11:11,208 --> 00:11:12,666
[EDOYAMA] Friends of my
daughter, you honor me.

209
00:11:12,750 --> 00:11:14,750
Welcome to our home.

210
00:11:21,250 --> 00:11:23,375
[MURASAKI] I should've
said something before.

211
00:11:23,458 --> 00:11:25,458
It's just that most people
get weird about it

212
00:11:25,541 --> 00:11:28,875
and I didn't want
to scare you guys off.

213
00:11:28,958 --> 00:11:31,333
Don't worry. It's okay.

214
00:11:31,416 --> 00:11:33,625
I don't expect to be liked.

215
00:11:36,291 --> 00:11:37,333
[RINKA]
We're not gonna blame you

216
00:11:37,416 --> 00:11:38,833
for who your parents are.

217
00:11:38,916 --> 00:11:41,041
C'mon. Give us a little credit.

218
00:11:41,125 --> 00:11:42,708
[MURASAKI]
Thank you.

219
00:11:43,791 --> 00:11:45,250
[RINKA] And since they
went to all this trouble

220
00:11:45,333 --> 00:11:46,708
we might as well eat, right?

221
00:11:46,791 --> 00:11:48,291
[MURASAKI] Yup! There's
more where this came from!

222
00:11:48,375 --> 00:11:49,875
[RINKA]
Woo hoo!

223
00:11:49,958 --> 00:11:52,583
[HOTOKEDA] It's been awhile
hasn't it, Boss Edoyama?

224
00:11:52,666 --> 00:11:54,708
You're Hotokeda,
if memory serves.

225
00:11:54,791 --> 00:11:56,833
What brings you here
all of a sudden?

226
00:11:56,916 --> 00:11:58,333
[HOTOKEDA]
Well...

227
00:11:58,416 --> 00:12:00,500
I figured I'd try to be a
gentleman, give you the courtesy

228
00:12:00,583 --> 00:12:02,333
of a quiet takeover
without all the fuss

229
00:12:02,416 --> 00:12:04,708
of an all-out turf war.

230
00:12:04,791 --> 00:12:06,166
I see.

231
00:12:06,250 --> 00:12:08,666
Think I'll just give you the
Kanto region, is that it?

232
00:12:08,750 --> 00:12:10,833
Yeah, that's more
or less the idea.

233
00:12:10,916 --> 00:12:14,208
I'll spare you the details,
but we've come up in the world.

234
00:12:14,291 --> 00:12:15,958
[KUROI]
I'm gonna take a leak.

235
00:12:19,125 --> 00:12:20,541
Ugh.

236
00:12:20,625 --> 00:12:22,083
I'm not the biggest fan of
yakuza, but this fat bastard's

237
00:12:22,166 --> 00:12:23,916
scummier than most of 'em.

238
00:12:24,000 --> 00:12:26,625
[RINKA] Got it. Down the hall,
and to the right.

239
00:12:27,833 --> 00:12:28,958
Uh--

240
00:12:29,041 --> 00:12:30,125
Hm?

241
00:12:31,791 --> 00:12:33,166
[RINKA, KUROI scream]

242
00:12:38,708 --> 00:12:39,750
Uh...?

243
00:12:39,833 --> 00:12:42,625
Wait, shouldn't you be in jail?

244
00:12:42,708 --> 00:12:44,666
[KYOTARO]
Is something wrong, or...?

245
00:12:44,750 --> 00:12:46,375
[MURASAKI, PEGGY]
Hm?

246
00:12:47,791 --> 00:12:49,916
[HOTOKEDA]
Well, it's about that time.

247
00:12:52,583 --> 00:12:53,833
[MURASAKI yelps]

248
00:12:53,916 --> 00:12:55,583
[KYOTARO grunts]

249
00:12:55,666 --> 00:12:57,125
[MURASAKI grunts]

250
00:12:57,208 --> 00:12:59,208
Help! Rinka!

251
00:12:59,291 --> 00:13:00,875
[RINKA]
Murasaki!

252
00:13:01,958 --> 00:13:03,500
[RINKA grunts]

253
00:13:03,583 --> 00:13:06,041
Guess who's suddenly
a big believer in karma?

254
00:13:06,125 --> 00:13:08,750
[RINKA grunting, panting]

255
00:13:08,833 --> 00:13:10,541
[KUROI]
I mean...

256
00:13:12,791 --> 00:13:15,000
[KUROI]
You can't ignore coincidence.

257
00:13:15,083 --> 00:13:17,041
What's goin' on out there?

258
00:13:17,125 --> 00:13:18,875
[HOTOKEDA]
Nothing all that special.

259
00:13:18,958 --> 00:13:22,041
Simple kidnapping
via teleportation.

260
00:13:25,666 --> 00:13:27,750
[MURASAKI, KYOTARO grunt]

261
00:13:27,833 --> 00:13:29,625
--[KYOTARO grunts]
--Kyotaro!

262
00:13:29,708 --> 00:13:30,708
[PEGGY]
Wah!

263
00:13:30,791 --> 00:13:32,458
Peggy, no!

264
00:13:33,708 --> 00:13:35,041
[HOTOKEDA]
There's no need for you to worry

265
00:13:35,125 --> 00:13:37,208
about your girl.
We'll take care of her.

266
00:13:37,291 --> 00:13:39,750
You just think things over.
Take your time.

267
00:13:39,833 --> 00:13:42,166
[EDOYAMA growls]

268
00:13:42,250 --> 00:13:44,791
[KUROI grunts]

269
00:13:44,875 --> 00:13:47,750
[RINKA grunts]

270
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:51,875
Why aren't her punches
passing through me?

271
00:13:51,958 --> 00:13:54,333
[KUROI] Looks like your power's
got some limits to it, babe.

272
00:13:54,416 --> 00:13:55,666
Heh.

273
00:13:55,750 --> 00:13:57,250
Walls you can pass through,
people not so much.

274
00:13:57,333 --> 00:13:59,500
Life's a bitch, princess.

275
00:13:59,583 --> 00:14:01,375
Now you tell me.

276
00:14:03,000 --> 00:14:05,333
[RINKA grunts]

277
00:14:05,416 --> 00:14:07,458
I've had just about
enough of you!

278
00:14:14,833 --> 00:14:16,166
What the--?

279
00:14:25,500 --> 00:14:26,625
Yeah, 'bout that.

280
00:14:26,708 --> 00:14:28,333
One of the details I was
hopin' to skip over

281
00:14:28,416 --> 00:14:30,416
in the interest
of doin' business.

282
00:14:30,500 --> 00:14:33,291
What the hell are you?

283
00:14:34,541 --> 00:14:35,833
I'm the guy who can give ya

284
00:14:35,916 --> 00:14:39,541
everything ya want. So hand over
the Kanto Territory.

285
00:14:39,625 --> 00:14:41,291
And not only do you
get your daughter back,

286
00:14:41,375 --> 00:14:44,250
I'll sell ya super powers
for a cool ten mill.

287
00:14:44,333 --> 00:14:45,916
It's a short term offer
and your daughter's life

288
00:14:46,000 --> 00:14:48,083
is on the line, so I imagine
you'll wanna decide

289
00:14:48,166 --> 00:14:49,958
'fore too long.

290
00:14:56,791 --> 00:14:59,416
[KYOTARO grunts]

291
00:14:59,500 --> 00:15:01,000
[MURASAKI grunts]

292
00:15:01,083 --> 00:15:04,208
[MURASAKI]
Let go! Kyotaro!

293
00:15:04,291 --> 00:15:05,875
[WINGED MASK]
Don't get involved, Kyotaro.

294
00:15:05,958 --> 00:15:08,000
She's not worth it.

295
00:15:09,250 --> 00:15:10,750
[KYOTARO]
Murasaki!

296
00:15:12,958 --> 00:15:16,958
It's weird, but I feel like
I know who that kidnapper is.

297
00:15:21,666 --> 00:15:23,583
Wait. This...

298
00:15:23,666 --> 00:15:25,291
This is our apartment building.

299
00:15:25,375 --> 00:15:28,625
[KUROI] Huh. So your name
is Rinka Urushiba.

300
00:15:28,708 --> 00:15:30,208
[RINKA]
Uh--

301
00:15:36,291 --> 00:15:38,083
You don't have to
go through with this!

302
00:15:38,166 --> 00:15:39,833
Wish I could say
it's not personal.

303
00:15:39,916 --> 00:15:42,916
But when you get down
to it, it kinda is.

304
00:15:43,000 --> 00:15:45,333
Ha! Burn baby, burn!

305
00:15:46,875 --> 00:15:48,625
[RINKA gasps]

306
00:15:55,541 --> 00:15:57,416
Dad, get out of there!

307
00:16:00,458 --> 00:16:01,958
[KUROI] Unless you want
more where that came from,

308
00:16:02,041 --> 00:16:05,291
honey, I suggest you stay
out of my goddamn way.

309
00:16:13,875 --> 00:16:17,916
[RINKA]
Daddy. I'm so sorry.

310
00:16:18,000 --> 00:16:20,416
This is what happens
when I get involved.

311
00:16:20,500 --> 00:16:22,500
It's my fault.

312
00:16:24,333 --> 00:16:28,041
[RINKA sobbing]
The people close to me get hurt.

313
00:16:28,125 --> 00:16:30,583
Who did I think I was?

314
00:16:30,666 --> 00:16:33,291
[RINDOU yells]

315
00:16:35,000 --> 00:16:36,291
Dad, you're okay!

316
00:16:36,375 --> 00:16:39,041
[RINDOU] Somebody call
the fire department!

317
00:16:39,125 --> 00:16:41,916
Thank goodness.
I thought I'd lost him.

318
00:16:46,333 --> 00:16:47,666
[KYOTARO]
Oh my god!

319
00:16:47,750 --> 00:16:49,000
[RINDOU]
Huh?

320
00:16:54,750 --> 00:16:58,583
They didn't get you.
I'm so glad.

321
00:16:59,791 --> 00:17:01,125
[KYOTARO gasps]

322
00:17:02,750 --> 00:17:04,333
[YOUNG KYOTARO]
Paulo!

323
00:17:06,125 --> 00:17:08,125
[YOUNG KYOTARO gasps]

324
00:17:08,208 --> 00:17:10,375
Don't die on me! Please!

325
00:17:13,166 --> 00:17:14,875
[RINDOU] Give me one
good reason I shouldn't

326
00:17:14,958 --> 00:17:17,041
rearrange your face
for gettin' my daughter

327
00:17:17,125 --> 00:17:18,791
mixed up in this crap!

328
00:17:18,875 --> 00:17:20,500
[RINKA]
Stop it!

329
00:17:20,583 --> 00:17:22,791
This isn't the time for
you to go all alpha male!

330
00:17:22,875 --> 00:17:25,916
A little girl's been kidnapped.
We need a rescue plan!

331
00:17:26,000 --> 00:17:27,625
[RINDOU grunts]

332
00:17:27,708 --> 00:17:30,583
Well, if we knew who did it,
we'd have someplace to start.

333
00:17:30,666 --> 00:17:32,000
[RINKA]
Hm...

334
00:17:32,083 --> 00:17:34,041
If nothing else, we should
at least call the police,

335
00:17:34,125 --> 00:17:36,416
don't you think?

336
00:17:36,500 --> 00:17:40,500
Hotokeda! That was
the ringleader's name!

337
00:17:40,583 --> 00:17:41,791
That's all we need to know!

338
00:17:41,875 --> 00:17:44,416
That fat bastard runs
the scene in Otsuka.

339
00:17:44,500 --> 00:17:46,625
[KYOTARO grunts]

340
00:17:46,708 --> 00:17:50,541
I'll go take care of it.
You guys stay here.

341
00:17:50,625 --> 00:17:52,458
[RINKA]
Are you kidding me?

342
00:17:54,625 --> 00:17:56,458
Rinka! Sweetie!

343
00:17:58,791 --> 00:18:02,416
[RINKA] This is my fault.
I should've protected her.

344
00:18:02,500 --> 00:18:06,458
They got her because
I screwed up. I failed!

345
00:18:06,541 --> 00:18:08,416
I'm not any kind of hero.

346
00:18:08,500 --> 00:18:09,541
God! Look at me!

347
00:18:09,625 --> 00:18:13,250
I can't even stand
on my own two feet!

348
00:18:13,333 --> 00:18:14,458
[MERAYAMA]
In ya go!

349
00:18:16,791 --> 00:18:17,875
Tell me where I am!

350
00:18:17,958 --> 00:18:19,291
What're you people
gonna do to me?

351
00:18:19,375 --> 00:18:20,833
I'll tell ya what we're gonna do

352
00:18:20,916 --> 00:18:24,375
if you don't shut that whiny
little trap o' yours, sweet pea.

353
00:18:27,583 --> 00:18:29,708
I'll burn ya so good,
they'll have to bust out

354
00:18:29,791 --> 00:18:31,416
dental records to I.D. ya.

355
00:18:31,500 --> 00:18:33,250
[KUROI] So ya think
ya can sell superpowers

356
00:18:33,333 --> 00:18:35,375
to any schmo with a wad a' cash?

357
00:18:35,458 --> 00:18:37,875
Cause it sounds bunk to me.

358
00:18:39,500 --> 00:18:40,791
[HOTOKEDA]
You won't care how it sounds

359
00:18:40,875 --> 00:18:42,291
once the money
starts rollin' in.

360
00:18:42,375 --> 00:18:44,416
But how's it even possible?

361
00:18:48,083 --> 00:18:49,291
These little fish
are about to be

362
00:18:49,375 --> 00:18:51,541
the hottest commodity
you've ever seen.

363
00:18:51,625 --> 00:18:54,041
People'll lose their
minds over 'em.

364
00:18:55,333 --> 00:18:56,833
All we need is
someone on the street

365
00:18:56,916 --> 00:18:58,958
who knows how to push product.

366
00:19:00,458 --> 00:19:02,541
[HOTOKEDA]
Merayama.

367
00:19:02,625 --> 00:19:04,250
Go check out our new digs.

368
00:19:04,333 --> 00:19:06,208
Kill anyone from the old guard.

369
00:19:06,291 --> 00:19:08,416
I don't want any legacy costs.

370
00:19:08,500 --> 00:19:09,583
[MERAYAMA]
Right.

371
00:19:14,541 --> 00:19:15,500
[MERAYAMA gasps]

372
00:19:19,250 --> 00:19:21,541
[MERAYAMA] You do all this
on your own, little birdie?

373
00:19:21,625 --> 00:19:23,166
[KYOTARO] Tell me where
you're keeping the girl.

374
00:19:23,250 --> 00:19:25,416
I've got no time for games.

375
00:19:25,500 --> 00:19:27,041
[MERAYAMA]
You think it's that simple?

376
00:19:27,125 --> 00:19:30,083
Clockin' a few guys
ain't enough incentive.

377
00:19:32,000 --> 00:19:33,750
[KYOTARO]
Tell me where she is, dammit!

378
00:19:33,833 --> 00:19:36,000
[MERAYAMA]
Ugh. Knock it off, kid.

379
00:19:36,083 --> 00:19:38,708
Look at'cha. You ain't
held a gun before.

380
00:19:38,791 --> 00:19:40,083
[MERAYAMA gasps]

381
00:19:40,166 --> 00:19:44,291
[MERAYAMA groans]

382
00:19:44,375 --> 00:19:45,791
[KYOTARO]
That was a warning shot.

383
00:19:45,875 --> 00:19:48,375
Your kind has no surprises
in store for me.

384
00:19:48,458 --> 00:19:50,125
Not since I was kid.

385
00:19:50,208 --> 00:19:52,916
[MERAYAMA panting]

386
00:19:53,000 --> 00:19:55,041
So you prepared for this?

387
00:19:59,333 --> 00:20:00,583
This is some serious bullshit!

388
00:20:00,666 --> 00:20:02,458
How the hell am I
s'posed to dodge a guy

389
00:20:02,541 --> 00:20:04,583
who blips in and out
of thin air?

390
00:20:08,375 --> 00:20:12,291
[MERAYAMA grunts]

391
00:20:14,333 --> 00:20:16,625
Watch where you're goi--!

392
00:20:16,708 --> 00:20:19,791
Long time no see, Merayama.

393
00:20:19,875 --> 00:20:22,458
Oh shit! Old Man Urushiba!

394
00:20:22,541 --> 00:20:25,666
You burn my apartment building
down, you son of a bitch?

395
00:20:25,750 --> 00:20:27,333
I got no idea what
you're talkin' about,

396
00:20:27,416 --> 00:20:28,333
I swear it!

397
00:20:28,416 --> 00:20:29,541
[RINDOU]
Tell us where the girl is

398
00:20:29,625 --> 00:20:31,625
or I'll launch your
sorry ass into orbit!

399
00:20:31,708 --> 00:20:34,000
Don't test me, ya little shit!

400
00:20:35,416 --> 00:20:37,500
Thank goodness you're okay!

401
00:20:39,583 --> 00:20:41,833
Little out of character for you.

402
00:20:41,916 --> 00:20:44,541
Since when do
super heroes need guns?

403
00:20:45,875 --> 00:20:48,333
Depends on the people
they're up against.

404
00:20:48,416 --> 00:20:51,958
And it depends on
what's at stake.

405
00:20:52,041 --> 00:20:54,125
Whatever you say, I guess.

406
00:20:54,208 --> 00:20:56,708
[MURASAKI whimpering]

407
00:20:56,791 --> 00:21:00,083
[MURASAKI grunting]

408
00:21:01,958 --> 00:21:03,708
[MURASAKI]
Stop being a child for once.

409
00:21:03,791 --> 00:21:06,541
You're always such
a stupid liability.

410
00:21:07,583 --> 00:21:08,708
Kyotaro!

411
00:21:08,791 --> 00:21:10,083
[PEGGY]
Wah!

412
00:21:10,166 --> 00:21:11,500
Peggy, no!

413
00:21:14,083 --> 00:21:15,500
Gotta be strong.

414
00:21:15,583 --> 00:21:18,625
You've gotta stand up and get
yourself outta this mess!

415
00:21:20,500 --> 00:21:22,333
[KUROI] I'm gonna go
out on a limb and guess

416
00:21:22,416 --> 00:21:24,541
you're not exactly
from around here.

417
00:21:27,458 --> 00:21:29,083
The hell is that rock anyway?

418
00:21:29,166 --> 00:21:32,125
That how you caught all the
fish, or is that a trade secret?

419
00:21:32,208 --> 00:21:33,916
[WINGED MASK]
There's no need for you to know.

420
00:21:34,000 --> 00:21:35,958
The fish do what they please.

421
00:21:36,041 --> 00:21:39,041
They decide everything.

422
00:21:46,458 --> 00:21:47,416
Huh?

423
00:21:50,166 --> 00:21:55,166
[MURASAKI screams]

424
00:21:57,333 --> 00:22:00,541
[RINDOU] Alright. This is where
the sons a' bitches hide out.

425
00:22:00,625 --> 00:22:01,875
Kid.

426
00:22:01,958 --> 00:22:03,666
Get my daughter outta here
and take her to the bar.

427
00:22:03,750 --> 00:22:07,041
I'll save the girl. Bastards
won't see Rindou comin'!

428
00:22:07,125 --> 00:22:08,625
Dad, you can't
do this by yourself.

429
00:22:08,708 --> 00:22:10,083
Some of those guys are espers!

430
00:22:10,166 --> 00:22:12,166
I can't just sit and wait
for you to come back

431
00:22:12,250 --> 00:22:14,166
when I know you're
in over your head.

432
00:22:14,250 --> 00:22:15,916
[RINDOU]
Give your old man some credit.

433
00:22:16,000 --> 00:22:18,291
Try giving your daughter
some credit for once!

434
00:22:18,375 --> 00:22:21,000
You didn't train me
to be a bystander!

435
00:22:21,083 --> 00:22:23,291
Had to play that card.

436
00:22:24,666 --> 00:22:27,333
At least you come by that
pig-headedness honestly.

437
00:22:27,416 --> 00:22:29,041
[RINKA grunts]

438
00:22:29,125 --> 00:22:32,083
Now take her to the bar
like I asked you.

439
00:22:32,166 --> 00:22:32,791
Cut it out!

440
00:22:32,875 --> 00:22:34,500
[RINKA]
Oh! No way!

441
00:22:42,041 --> 00:22:43,458
Don't just stare.

442
00:22:43,541 --> 00:22:45,916
You got enough juice left to
teleport me inside or what?

443
00:22:46,000 --> 00:22:48,458
You and your father
have some issues.

444
00:22:50,291 --> 00:22:52,000
[RINKA]
Shut up.

445
00:22:52,083 --> 00:22:54,833
Do we or don't we
have a responsibility?

446
00:22:54,916 --> 00:22:56,583
You really want us to be heroes?

447
00:22:56,666 --> 00:22:58,500
Then we gotta move, now!

448
00:22:58,583 --> 00:23:00,291
What's gotten into you?

449
00:23:00,375 --> 00:23:03,041
Murasaki. We're saving her.

450
00:24:34,750 --> 00:24:37,958
[PEGGY] Scene Four:
The Rain, Ring, and Girl.

